==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Acidimetry
<hw>Ac`id*im"e*try</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>acidus</ets> acid + <ets>-metry</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>The measurement of the strength of acids, especially by a chemical
process based on the law of chemical combinations, or the fact that, to
produce a complete reaction, a certain definite weight of reagent is
required.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Ac`id*i*met"ric*al</wf>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acidity</ent>⟦br⟧
